Disney Cruise Tracker — Build & Deploy Reference
================================================

PREREQUISITES
  pip install -r requirements.txt
  (Coastline shapefile must be in data/coastlines/ne_110m_land.shp)


FULL BUILD (run all steps)
  python build.py --all \
    --csv  data/2025-08-26_1907_ALL_SHIPS.csv \
    --coast data/coastlines/ne_110m_land.shp


INDIVIDUAL STEPS
  Step 1 — Parse new scraper CSV into assignments + cruise stubs:
    python build.py --step ingest --csv data/NEW_SCRAPE.csv

  Step 2 — Geocode any new ports (internet required for unknown ports):
    python build.py --step geocode

  Step 3 — Compute water-safe routes + build itinerary positions:
    python build.py --step route --coast data/coastlines/ne_110m_land.shp

  Step 4 — Export per-ship gzipped JSON to site/data/:
    python build.py --step export


INCREMENTAL UPDATE WORKFLOW
  1. Run your scraper and save new CSV to data/
  2. python build.py --all --csv data/NEW_DATE_ALL_SHIPS.csv \
                     --coast data/coastlines/ne_110m_land.shp
     (only new sailings are processed; all cached routes reused)
  3. git add site/data/ data/assignments.json data/routes_cache.json
  4. git commit -m "Data refresh YYYY-MM-DD"
  5. git push
     → GitHub Actions deploys to ships.coziahr.com automatically


LOCAL PREVIEW
  python -m http.server 8000 --directory site
  Open: http://localhost:8000


TUNE ROUTING QUALITY (slower but more accurate routes)
  python build.py --step route \
    --coast data/coastlines/ne_110m_land.shp \
    --hex-km 10 --buffer-km 6 --pad-deg 14 --verbose
  (Routes are cached; only uncomputed legs pay the cost)


REBUILD ALL ROUTES FROM SCRATCH
  python build.py --step route \
    --coast data/coastlines/ne_110m_land.shp \
    --rebuild-all --verbose


GITHUB + DNS SETUP (one time)
  1. Create GitHub repo, push this project
  2. Settings → Pages → Source: GitHub Actions
  3. In Dreamhost DNS: add CNAME  ships.coziahr.com → <user>.github.io
  4. In GitHub repo Settings → Pages → Custom domain: ships.coziahr.com


DATA NOTES
  - cruise_tracker.db is local only (gitignored). It is auto-created on first run.
  - data/routes_cache.json is committed to git (expensive to recompute).
  - 23 cruise types still have empty legs — ships on those routes won't appear.
    To fix, edit data/cruises/<slug>.json and fill in the "legs" array.
    See any filled cruise JSON for the format.
